After Henry (radio series).label: After Henry
After Henry (radio series).description:
After Henry was a British sitcom written by Simon Brett. It started on BBC Radio 4 and later moved to television. Prunella Scales and Joan Sanderson starred in both radio and television versions.
A novel, also by Simon Brett, followed the series. Wikipedia

Hancock's Half Hour.label: Hancock's Half Hour
Hancock's Half Hour.description: Hancock's Half Hour is a BBC radio comedy, and later television comedy, series of the 1950s and 60s written by Ray Galton and Alan Simpson. Wikipedia

Genius (radio series).label: Genius
Genius (radio series).description: Genius is a BBC Radio 4 comedy gameshow presented by comedian Dave Gorman. Listeners send in 'genius' ideas which are considered by Gorman and a guest before a studio audience, with a different guest for each show. Wikipedia

Just a Minute.label: Just a Minute
Just a Minute.description: Just a Minute is a BBC Radio 4 radio comedy and television panel game chaired by Nicholas Parsons. Its first transmission on Radio 4 was on 22 December 1967, three months after the station's launch. Wikipedia

Chambers (series).label: Chambers
Chambers (series).description: Chambers was a BBC radio and television sitcom. It was written by barrister Clive Coleman and starred John Bird and Sarah Lancashire in both versions. Wikipedia

Living with the Enemy.label: Living with the Enemy
Living with the Enemy.description: Living with the Enemy is a 2005 film starring Sarah Lancaster as Allison Conner, a young woman who meets a handsome software billionaire, Phillip Lauder, while attending a technology conference with her boss. Wikipedia

The Burkiss Way.label: The Burkiss Way
The Burkiss Way.description: The Burkiss Way is a BBC Radio 4 sketch comedy series, originally broadcast between August 1976 and November 1980. Wikipedia

Absolute Power (comedy).label: Absolute Power
Absolute Power (comedy).description: Absolute Power is a British comedy series, set in the offices of Prentiss McCabe, a fictional public relations company in London, run by Charles Prentiss and Martin McCabe. Wikipedia

Getting Nowhere Fast.label: Getting Nowhere Fast
Getting Nowhere Fast.description:
Getting Nowhere Fast is a BBC Radio sitcom written by and starring the comedian and musician Mervyn Stutter.
Stutter plays "Merv" the co-owner and manager of "The Cyber Pass", a former "vodka'n'veggies" bistro converted into an Internet Cafe. Wikipedia

The Grumbleweeds Radio Show.label: The Grumbleweeds Radio Show
The Grumbleweeds Radio Show.description: The Grumbleweeds' Radio Show was a long-running comedy sketch show that aired for fifteen series between 1979 and 1988, starring The Grumbleweeds and broadcast on BBC Radio 2. The show title was later shortened to The Grumbleweeds. Wikipedia

Married (radio series).label: Married
Married (radio series).description: Married is a BBC radio comedy with science fiction themes, first aired on BBC Radio 4. The main character is Robin Lightfoot, a confirmed bachelor with a successful architectural practice, who wakes up ... Wikipedia

Mitch Benn's Crimes Against Music.label: Mitch Benn's Crimes Against Music
Mitch Benn's Crimes Against Music.description: Mitch Benn's Crimes Against Music is a BBC Radio 4 comedy series, taking a satirical look at popular music. It is written by and stars Mitch Benn and Robin Ince. It also features Mitch's group The Distractions and in the first two series Alfie Joey. Wikipedia

The Navy Lark.label: The Navy Lark
The Navy Lark.description: The Navy Lark was a radio sit-com about life aboard a British Royal Navy frigate named HMS Troutbridge, based in HMNB Portsmouth. In series 1 and 2, the ship and crew were stationed offshore at an unnamed location known simply as "The Island". Wikipedia
